# Stack (Flowboard)

Use this rule when adding dependencies, choosing patterns, or answering questions about the project's technology choices.

## Framework & language

- **React** 19.x — UI framework
- **TypeScript** 5.x — strict mode, `verbatimModuleSyntax`, ES2022
- **Build:** Vite 7 with `@tailwindcss/vite` and `vite-tsconfig-paths`

## Routing

- **React Router 7.12** — file-based routing via `flatRoutes()` (see `frontend/app/routes.ts`)
- **SSR:** enabled in `react-router.config.ts`
- Route files: `_auth.*` for auth layout, `_app/route.tsx` for app layout, `$param` for dynamic segments

## Styling

- **Tailwind CSS 4** — via `@tailwindcss/vite`
- **Utilities:** `cn()` from `~/lib/utils` (clsx + tailwind-merge) for all className merging
- **Design tokens:** CSS variables in `app/app.css`; task colors in `app/lib/design-tokens.ts`

## Component library

- **Radix UI** primitives — Dialog, Select, Popover, Dropdown, Tabs, Alert Dialog, Collapsible, etc.
- **shadcn-style** wrappers in `app/components/ui/` (Button, Card, Input, Select, Sheet, etc.)
- **Variants:** class-variance-authority (cva) for Button, Badge, etc.
- **Icons:** inline SVGs or lucide-react where used (e.g. Calendar, task-detail-sheet)

## State management

- **Zustand** — auth token (`stores/auth.store.ts`), theme (`stores/theme.store.ts`)
- **TanStack Query** — all server state (workspaces, boards, tasks, profile)
- **useState** — local UI state (modals, form fields)

## Forms & validation

- **TanStack Form** + **Zod** (e.g. create-workspace-modal)
- **Zod** for schema validation with `@tanstack/zod-form-adapter`

## HTTP & API

- **Axios** — single instance in `app/lib/axios.ts` with auth interceptors and refresh
- **API modules:** `auth-api.ts`, `workspace-api.ts`, `task-api.ts` in `app/lib/`

## Backend

- **NestJS 11** — feature modules: auth, board, task, users, workspace, mail, health
- **TypeORM** — PostgreSQL, entities per domain
- **Validation:** class-validator, Joi for env

## Path alias

- `~/*` → `frontend/app/*` (see `frontend/tsconfig.json`)
